# Sephr — 003-screen-ai-disable-guard
#
# ungoogled-chromium's disable-ai.patch drops the chrome/browser/screen_ai
# target group (no screen_ai_install_state, no screen_ai_service_router).
# But chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc still calls
# screen_ai::ScreenAIInstallState::GetInstance() inside the kScreenAI
# sandbox spawn branch — an unresolved symbol in the final framework link.
#
# Replace the body with a VLOG + early return. The kScreenAI sandbox type
# is never actually spawned at runtime because the component path is empty
# (its installer target was dropped), so this branch is unreachable except
# defensively.

